        "text": "putting them to shame",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the mind of the apostle, was not an end, but a means, as he says also on another occasion, that he was unwilling to make them sad, though he had actually done so. The apostle often introduces a certain degree of refined pleasantry, without forgetting the apostolic gravity, for example, ",
